iddle of the Linked List — Floyd’s Slow & Fast Pointer Technique
This solution finds the middle node of a singly linked list.
Two pointers are used:

slow → moves 1 step at a time
fast → moves 2 steps at a time

When fast reaches the end, slow will be at the middle.
For even-length lists, this returns the second middle node, as required by LeetCode.
Complexity

Time Complexity: O(n) — each node is visited at most once.
Space Complexity: O(1) — uses only two pointers.


class Solution {
    public ListNode middleNode(ListNode head) {
        if(head==null|| head.next==null) return head;
        ListNode fast=head;
        ListNode slow=head;
        while(fast!=null && fast.next!=null){
            slow=slow.next;
            fast=fast.next.next;
        }
        return slow;
        
    }
}
